{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Pause NHS Neighbourhood plans, protect local GP surgeries & hold consultation",
        "additional_details": "We are concerned that the reforms could:\r\nLead to closing or merging local GP surgeries\r\nEnd continuity of care with family doctors\r\nForce patients to travel further for appointments\r\nBankrupt GP practices and force them shut as warned by the BMA\r\nHand contracts to struggling hospital trusts or private firms\r\nRisk longer waits, poorer access and loss of trusted local care for patients\r\n \r\nWe call for an immediate pause, a full public consultation, protection for GP surgeries, and for the Government to formally guarantee that contracts will not be handed to private companies.",
        "background": "Pause the rollout of Neighbourhood Health reforms. Hold a full public consultation, publish detailed implementation plans, commit to protecting GP surgeries, and formally commit to and guarantee that no contracts will be handed to private companies or overstretched hospital trusts.",
